<TITLE>
Preparatory Meeting to the 3rd Annual Conference of the Convention On Biological Diversity
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 
<BODY BACKGROUND="/graphics/back.gif" background="/graphics/back.gif" 
BGCOLOR="#ffffff"  link="#215e21"  vlink="#215e21" alink="#a67d3d">

<center><img src="/graphics/tit_nwr2.gif" alt="WWF News Releases">


<table width=580>
<td>
<CENTER><h2>Preparatory Meeting to the 3rd Annual Conference of the Convention On Biological Diversity
<BR>
</h2></CENTER>
<P>
<B>WHAT: <BR>
</B>
<P>
WWF will be taking an active part in the deliberations of the
Second  Meeting of the Subsidiary Body on Scientific, Technical
and Technological Advice (SBSTTA) of the Convention on Biological
Diversity (CBD). The meeting will provide advice and inputs to
the third Conference of Parties of the CBD to be held in Buenos
Aires, Argentina (4-15 November 1996).<BR>

<P>
WWF will be presenting the following papers at the meeting:
<ul>
<li>Incentives for Conservation and Sustainable Use of Biodiversity: Implementing Article 11 of the CBD
<li>Protecting Forest Biodiversity: The Role of the CBD
<li>Measuring Forest Quality: Criteria and Indicators for Forests
<li>Linking Protected Areas and People: Implementing Art 8 on In&#173;Situ Conservation
</ul>  <BR>

<P>
Just prior to the SBSTTA meeting, the fourth session of the Global
Biodiversity  Forum will be held at the Palais des Congr&egrave;s
in Montreal (31 August-1 September  1996). WWF is co-organizing
the following three workshops at the Forum: <B> Incentives for
conservation of  biodiversity ; New methods for linking people
and protected areas;</B> and<B> Forest Biodiversity. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</B>
<P>
<B>WHERE:</B>
<p>
 Montreal Convention Centre, 201 Viger West (Tel:
+1 514 871 8122)<BR>

<P>
<B>WHO:<BR>
</B>
<P>
The WWF team at SBSTTA will include Catalina Toro of WWF Colombia
Programme Office, Nurit Bensusan of  WWF Brazil, ErieTamale of
 Eastern Africa Regional Programme, Jeanne Zoundjihekpon of  WWF
Cote d'Ivoire, Wendy Yap  of WWF Malaysia, Tony Adisoemarto of
 WWF Indonesia Programme, Estherine Lisinge of  WWF Cameroon,
Rai Rana of WWF India, Steve Howard and Niall Watson of WWF UK,
Elba Alissie Fiallo of  Fundacion Natura, and Nancy Vallejo and
Gonzalo Oviedo of WWF International.<BR>

<P>
For more information before the meeting, please contact Someshwar
Singh at +41 22 364 9553, during the meeting Nancy Vallejo at
+1 514 878 9888 and fax +1 514 878 6341. For copies of the WWF
papers, please call Delwyn Dupuis at +41 22 364 9517.
<P>
<font size=-1>
In the US and Canada, WWF is referred to as the World Wildlife Fund.
</font>

