<P>
<B>(Concept) RU0038 Russian Federation: Management Planning for
Yamalsky and Gydansky Reserves in the Russian Arctic</B><!--RU0038 Russian Federation Management Planning for Yamalsky and Gydansky Reserves in the Russian Arctic-->
<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<U><B>Project Summary</B></U><B>:</B>
<P>
This one-year project will provide supervisory and facilitative
support to the preparation of a management plan for Yamalsky and
Gydansky Reserves in the Russian Arctic. The plan will concentrate
in particular on management of this large territory, wildlife
monitoring programmes, and involving local indigenous people (Nentsy)
in measures to protect the reserves and make sustainable use of
their natural resources. <BR>

<TABLE>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307><U><B>Priority Biomes</B></U><B>    <U>%</U></B>
</TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD><TD WIDTH=307><U><B>Strategies</B></U><B>    <U>%</U></B>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307>Forests     0</TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD><TD WIDTH=307>Consumption &amp; Pollution 0
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307>Freshwater Ecosystems  0</TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD>
<TD WIDTH=307>EE &amp; Capacity Building  0</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307>Oceans and Coasts   100</TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD>
<TD WIDTH=307>Protected Areas    70</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307>Non-Priority Biomes  0</TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD>
<TD WIDTH=307>Species     0</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307>Non-Biome Specific  0</TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD>
<TD WIDTH=307>Sustainable Resource Use 30</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307></TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD><TD WIDTH=307>Treaties &amp; Legislation  0
