<P>
<U><B>Project Background:</B></U>
<P>
Placement of an education officer for Asia/Pacific within one
of the WWF NOs is viewed as an effective way to achieve decentralization
to the field and full integration of education and capacity building
with the Asia/Pacific Programme. Projects of greater relevance
at the grass roots level and significant for achieving WWF's Mission
will be produced. The post will also facilitate better networking
of WWF education officers in the region, as well as making project
supervision easier.<BR>

<P>
<U><B>Project Objectives:</B></U>
<P>
1.  To plan, develop, supervise, and coordinate Asia/Pacific education
projects within the overall education programme, under direction
from the Environmental Education and Conservation Capacity Building
(EE&amp;CCB) department, and in accordance with the WWF Asia/Pacific
Programme.
<P>
2.  To assist with, and participate in, regional education and
capacity building programme planning. This includes the review
of proposals, preparation of education projects and programme
budgets, and development of new concepts and descriptions.
<P>
3.  To promote collaboration, links, integrated projects, and
circulation of ideas and materials between WWF NOs and selected
NGOs in the Asia/Pacific region. 
<P>
4.  To promote a &quot;WWF Asia/Pacific Education and Capacity
Building Network&quot;. This includes representatives of WWF&#173;Australia,
WWF&#173;Hong Kong, WWF&#173;India, WWF&#173;Japan, WWF&#173;Malaysia,
WWF-New&#173;Zealand, WWF&#173;Pakistan, and selected WWF Programme
Offices.
<P>
5.  To undertake other activities within the WWF Education and
Capacity Building Programme, as per agreement with the education
coordinator at the International Secretariat.
<P>
6.  To liaise closely with other divisions and staff of the International
Secretariat (Communications, Fundraising and Development, International
Policy, etc.).<BR>
<BR>

