<P>
<U><B>Project Background:</B></U>
<P>
The conceptualization of this project was motivated by the December
1994 agreement of the Mekong countries to revitalize the Mekong
Secretariat, and by the need to implement the WWF agenda on freshwater
ecosystems. However, the most important consideration is the fact
that the Mekong River is crucial to the economic life of Indochina.
It is perhaps the best place to realize the ideals of sustainable
development.<BR>

<P>
<U><B>Project Objectives:</B></U>
<P>
1.  To conduct a preliminary study of the project area and to
develop a funding proposal.
<P>
2.  To conduct an ecological inventory of the river and its watersheds,
and to develop a biodiversity conservation programme.
<P>
3.  To institutionalize the conservation and sustainable financing
mechanisms.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<I><B>9S0717.1: Biodiversity Studies of the Mekong River and Watershed
(Jul. 95 - Jul. 99</B>)<BR>
<BR>
</I>
<P>
<U><I><B>Activity Background:</B></I></U>
<P>
See Project Background.<BR>

<P>
<U><I><B>Activity Objectives:</B></I></U>
