<TD WIDTH=307>Protected Areas    0</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307>Non-Priority Biomes  100</TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD>
<TD WIDTH=307>Species     0</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307>Non-Biome Specific  0</TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD>
<TD WIDTH=307>Sustainable Resource Use 0</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307></TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD><TD WIDTH=307>Treaties &amp; Legislation  100
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=307></TD><TD WIDTH=28></TD><TD WIDTH=307>Non-Priority Strategies  0
</TD></TR>

</TABLE>

<P>
<U><B>Project Background:</B></U>
<P>
The inspiration for this project comes from two initiatives of
the Asia/Pacific Programme: the model IPAS Legislation Project
and the project on the marine turtle transborder sanctuary between
Malaysia and the Philippines. Difficult legal issues can often
delay the implementation of projects, and the lessons learned
from the experience of these two projects and other transborder
initiatives could be consolidated into a model agreement which
could facilitate future negotiations. <BR>

<P>
<U><B>Project Objectives:</B></U>
<P>
1.  To formulate a model multilateral transborder protected areas
agreement.
<P>
2.  To publish and circulate the model.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<I><B>9S0721.1: Model Agreement on Transborder Reserves (Jul.
95 - Jun. 96</B>)<BR>
<BR>
</I>
<P>
<U><I><B>Activity Background:</B></I></U>
<P>
See Project Background.<BR>

<P>
<U><I><B>Activity Objectives:</B></I></U>
<P>
See Project Objectives.<BR>
