<title>

Whales In The Wild

</title>

</head>

<body background="/graphics/back.gif" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff">

<center>

<table cellpadding=10 width=510>

<td align=left>



<table cellpadding=10 width=500>


<tr><td align=left>





<center><h1><b>Whales In The Wild</b></h1></center>

<hr size=1 noshade>

<tt><font size=2><b>by Elizabeth Kemf and Cassandra Phillips</b></font></tt>

<p>



<br>

<tt> A WWF Species Status Report

<p>

<img align=right src="wanted.jpeg" alt="Wanted Alive!">


<br>


<ul>

<li><b><a href="page2.htm"> Executive Summary</a>

<p>

<li><a href="page3.htm">The Whale in History and Culture</a>

<p>

<li><a href="page4.htm">WWF's Campaign for Whale Conservation</a>

<p>

<li><a href="page5.htm">What WWF is Doing</a>

<p>

<li><a href="page6.htm">The Threats Facing Whales</a>

<p>

<li><a href="page7.htm">The Status of the Great Whales</a>

<p>

<li><a href="page8.htm">What Needs to be Done</a></b></tt>


</ul>



<p>


<br>


<br>


About the authors: Elizabeth Kemf, Species Conservation Coordinator for WWF International, was the WWf representative to the International Whaling Commision from 1982 to 1991.  She has worked on whale and dolphin conservation issues since 1974 and has participated in WWF's non-leathal benign whale research in the Indian and Pacific Oceans.

<p>

Cassandra Phillips, Anartic and Cetacean Officer for WWF International, has been WWF representative to the International Whaling Commission since 1992, and was a member of the UK delegation to the IWC from 1984 to 1991.  She has visited the Antarctic twice as an environmental observer at the invitation of the British Antarctic Survey. 

<p>

<br>




<hr size=1 noshade>


<font size=2><tt> Published in October 1994 by WWF-World Wide Fund For Nature
(known in the USA and Canada as World Wildlife Fund), Gland, Switzerland. Any reproduction in full or in part of this publication must mention the title and credit the above-mentioned publisher as the copyright owner.</tt></font>



</td></tr>

