<blockquote><blockquote>
<P>
In Table A.1 it is shown in which sectors of the economy the employment
is generated, which is the result of an increase and decrease
in investment in a number of sectors of the Dutch economy. The
results incorporate the employment generated abroad. The sectors
printed on the upper side of the table are the sectors in which
the investments take place. The sectors on the left-hand side
of the table are the sectors in which employment is generated.
The respending of money saved on energy bills (9.23 billion guilders),
internal costs (0.40 billion guilders) and costs of interest (0.76
billion guilders) are invested in the sector 'Total economy'.
The numbers printed on the lower side of the table give the employment
which is the result of a particular investment. The numbers on
the right-hand side give the total employment generated in a sector
as a result of all investments.
<P>
<b>Table A.1</b><i> Direct and indirect employment potential of CO<sub>2</sub>-reduction
measures</i><p>

