<TITLE>Fact Sheet: Brown Bear</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/graphics/back.gif" bgcolor=#ffffff>
<center><img src="/graphics/fct_panda.gif" alt="Fact Sheet"></center>
<hr noshade width=506>
<center><font size=6>BROWN BEARS</font></center>
<hr noshade width=506>

<center><table border=0 width=506><td><br>
<P>

<B>CAPTIVE BREEDING<BR>
</B>
<P>
Brown Bears are held within many zoological collections. Generally,
it is difficult to determine which of these are of European origin.
The 1992 International Zoo Yearbook records the birth of 2 Brown
Bear cubs of the Pyrenean form, at Berne (Switzerland).<SUP>29
<BR>
</SUP>


<p>
<hr noshade width=506>

</td>
