<P>
The total Brown Bear population in wider Europe has been estimated
at 46,000.<SUP>12</SUP> A total of between 130 and 200 bears are
estimated to live in the four fragmented populations remaining
in western Europe. National estimates are not yet available for
all parts of the former USSR, former Yugoslavia, or the two parts
of former Czechoslovakia.<SUP>12<BR>
</SUP>
<P>
<B>Major population:</B> There are an estimated 35,000 Brown Bears
in Russia west of the Urals, and this is by far the largest national
Brown Bear population in Europe. No information is available on
areas of key importance for bears.<SUP>12<BR>


