<center>
<table width="580">
<tr><td colspan="2" align="middle"><img src="/graphics/employ2.JPG">

<tr>
<td align="middle" valign="bottom">
<h2>WWF Is Seeking</h2>
<br>
<h3>
Campaign Director WWF 2000
</h3>

<td align="middle" valign="top"><IMG SRC="/graphics/logo3.gif">

<tr><td colspan="2">
<p>
<br>
WWF - World Wide Fund for Nature is the largest
international conservation organisation in the world.
In October this year the "Living Planet Campaign"
was launched to mobilize global action to protect
endangered spaces and species; to change the
way we use resources from the forests and oceans,
and to reduce the quantities of oil and coal we burn.
<p>
The Campaign Team is based in the Netherlands
and now that its start-up phase has been
completed, we are looking for a dynamic
<p>
<dd><b>CAMPAIGN DIRECTOR WWF 2000</b>
<p>
who will energetically lead the Campaign to a
triumphant conclusion in the year 2000 by creatively
highlighting on-going activities within, and outside
the WWF Network. The Director will be the driving
force behind the Campaign Team consisting of a
Campaign Manager, a Campaign Ambassador,
and up to 5 other staff members.
<p>
The primary task is to draw on the global WWF
Network to achieve tangible success in reaching
the three Campaign goals. The secondary task is
to develop communications strategies and tools to
ensure that the Campaign goals and results are
widely understood within, and outside the WWF
Network. A third task is to gain cooperation,
support and action from the leaders in the WWF
Network. The Campaign Director will be
responsible for the development and supervision of
the Campaign plans and budgets.
<p>
Because the Campaign depends heavily on the
ability to involve, and initiate action from, key
players in a diverse international organization we
are looking for a person with the following skills:
<ul type circle>
<p>
<li>Proven success in leadership, including
conceptual thinking and planning. 
<p>
<li>Successful history of managing campaigns or
action-oriented activities.
<p>
<li>An in-depth, substantive knowledge of key
international conservation issues.
<p>
<li>Demonstrated skills in translating technical
jargon into easy-to-understand and
easy-to-communicate goals and actions.
<p>
<li>Ability to facilitate discussions and reach
consensus in diverse groups. 
<p>
<li>Proven success in motivating staff.
<p>
<li>Perfect English plus knowledge of another
European language (Dutch would be an
advantage).
</ul>
<p>
Applicants should forward a cover letter and their
CV to Ms. Effie Blanchard, Human Resources,
WWF International, Avenue du Mont Blanc,
CH-1196 Gland, Switzerland,<br> 
(fax: +41 22 364 78 50), by 31 December 1996.
<p>
