<HEAD>

<TITLE>
Campaign Director WWF 2000
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/graphics/back.gif" BACKGROUND="/graphics/back.gif" 
background="/graphics/back.gif" BGCOLOR="#ffffff"     link="#ff0000"  
vlink="#ff0000" alink="#a67d3d">

<center>
<table width="580">
<tr><td colspan="2" align="middle"><img src="/graphics/employ2.JPG">

<tr>
<td align="middle" valign="bottom">
<h2>WWF Is Seeking</h2>
<br>
<h3>
Manager, Species Programme
</h3>

<td align="middle" valign="top"><IMG SRC="/graphics/logo3.gif">

<tr><td colspan="2">
<p>
<br>
There is a vacancy at WWF International for a
Manager, Species Programme, based in Gland,
Switzerland.   This will be a three-year appointment,
with the possibility of further extension.
<p>
The main role of the position will be to act as the
focus for species issues for the WWF International
Secretariat and provide leadership  to the  WWF
network on species conservation.   
<p>
The Manager, Species Programme, will serve as
Secretary to the WWF Species Advisory Group
(SAG) which provides policy guidance and advice
on species issues throughout the WWF network. 
The Manager will favour an  integrated approach to
species conservation that takes into account the
complex and often contradictory  views on species
conservation issues both within the WWF network
and the wider world.  Tasks will include policy and
advocacy work, as well as technical and logistical
support to WWF projects with a species
component around the world.  As a Head of Unit,
the Manager will be part of the management team
of the WWF International Secretariat.
<p>
Qualifications and experience required:
<p>
<ul type circle>
<li>a first degree, and preferably a higher degree
in some aspect of the species environment,
especially  if  it  is related to conservation or
resource use.
<p>
<li>a minimum of five years in one or more fields
of species conservation, with some proven
management experience of multi-project
programmes.
<p>
<li>a strong understanding of the following: 
species conservation issues;  protected area
management as it relates to species conservation;
integrated conservation and development
approaches and community conservation
techniques;  international treaties as they relate to
species conservation.
<p>
<li>a team builder with excellent diplomacy and
communication skills, credible personal
presentation, and the ability to build consensus.
<p>
<li>fluent English with other language skills an
advantage.
</ul>
<p>
Please send a covering letter with your c.v. to Ms
Effie Blanchard, WWF International, Avenue du
Mont Blanc, 1196 Gland, Switzerland. 
Fax:+41.22.364.78.50. The closing date for
applications is 31 December 1996.
<p>
</table>
<p>




