<h2>WWF Is Seeking</h2>
<br>
<h3>
Regional Coordinator for Central Indonesia
</h3>

<td align="middle" valign="top"><IMG SRC="/graphics/logo3.gif">

<tr><td colspan="2">
<p>
<br>
The World Wide Fund for Nature (WWF) Indonesia Program is seeking
qualified candidates for the position of Regional Coordinator for Central
Indonesia. The job will based in Jakarta. 
<p>
<b>RESPONSIBILITIES:</b>
<p>
Scope: Oversee and facilitate WWF-IP's project activities in central
Indonesia, including terrestrial projects located in Kalimantan, Sulawesi,
Java, Bali, and Nusa Tenggara. Programmatic areas include: terrestrial
biomes, forest conservation and forestry-related issues, aquatic/marine
conservation activities, community-based conservation and natural resource
management, integrated conservation and development projects,
conservation-oriented research. Responsible for tracking and monitoring
project-related correspondence with project donors, including quality and
timeliness of project reports.  Develop WWF-IP's policy initiatives for this
sub-region as they emerge from and relate to WWF-IP projects and interests.
Travel within this sub-region approximately 20-40% in the execution of
responsibilities.   
<p>
<b>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:</b>
<p>
The preferred candidate will possess the following qualifications: 8-10
years of experience in the conservation field, with specific experience in
field project management; masters degree or higher in a related conservation
field; strong organizational and interpersonal skills; strong written and
spoken language skills in both English and Indonesian; proficient processing
and spreadsheets; commitment to professionalism.  
