<html>
<head>
<title>Energy Efficiency In Poland</title>
</head>
<body background="/graphics/back.gif" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff">
<center>
<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=10 width=510>
<td align=left>

<center>
<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=12 width=480>
<tr><td align=left>

<h2>Energy efficiency in Poland</h2>

<p>

<hr size=1 noshade>

<p>
<br>

Poland's energy use fell by 22 per cent between 1989 and 1993 - a time of turmoil when industrial production was in decline. Although the economy is now recovering, energy intensity in industry has dropped by 20 per cent. The Polish Foundation for Energy Efficiency, supported by WWF, works to maintain the country's improved level of energy efficiency and ensure that environmental benefits accompany economic growth.

<p>

Since 1990, working with more than 20 financial, scientific, and institutional partners, the foundation has already :

<p>
<br>

<ul>

<li>completed an inventory of Poland's greenhouse
	gases

<p>

<li>carried out an evaluation of the potential for energy - efficiency measures and the profitability of new technologies for various  economic sectors

<p>

<li>produced energy audits for some major industrial facilities and public institutions such       	as hospitals and schools

<p>

<li>set up Katowice's Coalbed Methane Clearing - house

<p>

<li>established an energy education centre

<p>

<li>produced a series of 12 television programmes promoting energy conservation.

</ul>
<p>
<br>

WWF is currently helping the foundation distribute
energy - efficient light bulbs to areas of Warsaw where power cuts are frequent. If successful, demand for electricity should decrease by 25 per cent in these districts, obviating the need to build a new power plant. If this pilot project works, officials have agreed to extend it to other parts of Poland.

</ul>

<p>
<br>
<p>
<br>

<hr size=1 noshade>

<a href="page24-25.htm#one">Back to the previous page</a>

</td></tr>
</table>
</center>

</td>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<center><a href="/graphics/toolbar.map"><img src="/graphics/toolbar.gif" border=0 ISMAP></a><p>
<i><h6>Copyright 1996, The World Wide Fund For Nature</i></h6></center></body></html>
